race.comment: Open contest. MR O'REILLY (11) has a handy record over this track and trip with a win and a second from three attempts and will be rock-hard fit for this. Should get a cosy run in transit from gate three and will be rock there when the whips are cracking. CAPITAL ASSET (9) is one from one over this distance range and gets in well at the weights with the 2kg claim. Will give a great sight. The well-related LIVING FREE (1) (half to G1 winner Warning) saluted in Saturday metro grade last time out and will appreciate the drop back in company here. Top-three contender. WARP SPEED (3) also hails from a handy family (half to G1 winner Nom Du Jeu) and has placed two from three over this track and trip. In the mix. ARCHER'S GAME (5) is usually thereabouts and is one for the multiples.
